Rating: 4
Best. Dessert. Ever. I used chocolate graham cracker cookies instead of chocolate wafers, but I think that made it better. The vanilla pastry cream is especially good and very similar to what my mom used to fill her cream puffs with when I was a kid.

Rating: 3
The ganache is AH-MAZING. Not too sweet, just sweet enough, and the texture is to die for. Complemented nicely by the sweetness of the pastry cream. Some reviewers felt the pastry cream was too sweet, but with the semi-sweetness of the ganache I thought it was a perfect pairing. I made a graham cracker crust instead of the chocolate cookie crust called for in the recipe, which added a nice hint of salt that I thought rounded out the other two flavors well. I gave this 3 forks and not 4 for three reasons - the whipped cream, the presentation and the texture of the pastry cream. This DOES NOT need the whipped cream. At all. Definitely serve it ON THE SIDE - do not put it on the pie!!! Both the texture and the extra sweetness of the whipped cream pollute the deliciousness that is this pie, on its own. Other than that, I think this pie looks a little ugly. Next time I would skip the marbling and just leave the extra ganache nicely drizzled across the top and finish with banana slices, to make it look a little more refined. Also, the pastry cream did not set as much as I would have liked. But all in all, my husband freaked over this recipe and I thought it was pretty indulgent. Perfect for a barbeque or fried chicken night!

Rating: 4
I took a hint from a previous reviewer and turned this into a 9 x 13 dish (used glass ... the layers are lovely). I also substituted some coconut milk for the real milk in making the pudding part. That's a fun, tropical twist. When I marbled in the ganache, the effect was so pretty that I didn't want to cover it up with cream, so instead, I just served the whipped cream on the side. Considering I made the "pie" in about 1/2 hour (I was in a rush, so didn't do the full 'chill' in between), the taste and look was spectacular! Loved it.

