Rating: 4
Thanks to CNanceJD from Atlanta, GA, I was able to make this pie in one evening, shaving a couple of hours off the required time. I used a double chocolate sandwich cookie crust (24 cookies with 1/4 cup of butter(melted) and ground in the Cuisinart) instead of the crust listed here. I then followed CNanceJD's tips as follows: Chocolate ganache: microwave the cream and butter on medium in 30 second spurts and stir after each heating until it is hot, remove from the microwave and add the vanilla and dissolve in the chocolate. Pastry filling: heat everything except vanilla on high for 1 minute 5 times, whisking it after each minute to keep it smooth. I added an ounce of white chocolate to the pastry filling which I melted in while heating it; I highly recommend trying this. Remove filling from microwave and whisk in vanilla. My own tip - I put the pastry cream into the freezer for one hour, then the fridge for 1 1/2 hours to cut down some time. This pie took a long time, but is super easy and if you plan ahead (which I didn't) it would be a snap to make if done over two nights! I received RAVE reviews and 6 dinner guests ate the whole pie! It is rich but super delicious and impressive to look at, especially when you marbelize the ganache on top. I will make this one again and do over two nights - I want to make it soon! Follow these tips - DEE-LISH!

