Rating: 4
This pie is great. Chocolate and bananas really go together. A few modifications to the instructions make preparation a breeze. I made the crust from crumbs of fudge creme filled cookies-I ground up whole cookies (including filling) in a food processor along with a few tablespoons of melted butter to hold the crumbs together; this crust was really easy to make, cuts well and tasted great. You can also use the microwave to speed up making the ganache and pastry filling and to avoid the danger of burning. Chocolate ganache: microwave the cream and butter on medium in 30 second spurts and stir after each heating until it is hot, remove from the microwave and add the vanilla and dissolve in the chocolate. Pastry filling: heat everything except vanilla on high for 1 minute 5 times, whisking it after each minute to keep it smooth. I added an ounce of white chocolate to the pastry filling which I melted in while heating it; I highly recommend trying this. Remove filling from microwave and whisk in vanilla.

