Rating: 3
Everyone was so pleased with this pie. It is a wonderful variation on the traditional banana cream pie. But all the previous reviewers were right-- the crust is much too hard, making the pie nearly impossible to slice neatly. I recommend using the crust recipe from Bon Appetit's 1999 Black Bottom Chocolate Pie-- (only one ounce of chocolate, I think, and six tablespoons of butter, plus more cookie). It tastes just as good, but slices up much easier. I made this pie over three consecutive evenings: the pastry cream the first night, the ganache and pie crust on the second night, and the whipped cream on the third night. I assembled the pie on day three, (except for the whipped cream) and we ate it day four, right after I garnished with the cream (which I whipped again, as it lost volume overnight) and banana. Oh yes... do use very ripe bananas, otherwise their flavor will be lost.

